    <section class="section">
      <h2>Detailed Performance</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card card-plain">
          <h3>Image Quality</h3>
          <p>33MP offers plenty of crop potential. Colors are accurate and the RAW files are incredibly pliable. It is a
            significant step up from the 24MP of the A7 III.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-plain">
          <h3>Handling & Build</h3>
          <p>The deep grip is comfortable for all-day shooting with heavy lenses. The full-size HDMI port is a huge plus
            for video work compared to flimsy micro-HDMI ports.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card card-plain">
          <h3>Video Performance</h3>
          <p>Focus breathing compensation with Sony lenses is a game changer. Rolling shutter is noticeable in 4K24p
            full-frame, but the S35 4K60p image is stunningly detailed.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

